body:
Feature gate: `#![feature(float_minimum_maximum)]`

This is the tracking issue for the `f{32,64}::{min,max}imum` functions.

It provide IEEE 754-2019 `minimum` and `maximum` functions to f32/f64.

### Public API

```rust
impl f32 {
    pub fn minimum(self, other: f32) -> f32;
    pub fn maximum(self, other: f32) -> f32;
}

impl f64 {
    pub fn minimum(self, other: f64) -> f64;
    pub fn maximum(self, other: f64) -> f64;
}
```

### Steps / History

- [x] Implementation: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/91008
- [ ] Final comment period (FCP)
- [ ] Stabilization PR

### Unresolved Questions

- Should the implementation be stabilized in it's current state (ie. without intrinsic: [explanation](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/91079#issuecomment-975194047) and [llvm issue](https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/53353)) ?
- Should it be called like IEEE 754-2019 (`minimum` and `maximum`) or something else ? https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/91079#issuecomment-1127065158
- Should the standard library have this function at all (we already have `min`/`max`) ?
